# Supabase PostgreSQL Extensions — Search, IDs, Audit & Geo

---

## pg_hashids — Short Human-Readable IDs

**When you need it**: Public-facing URLs that shouldn't expose sequential IDs (`/orders/1`, `/orders/2` reveals order count). Convert integer IDs to short strings like `jR`, `k3L`.

```sql
CREATE EXTENSION IF NOT EXISTS pg_hashids WITH SCHEMA extensions;

-- Encode integer → short string
SELECT extensions.id_encode(1);           -- 'jR'
SELECT extensions.id_encode(100);         -- 'Lw'
SELECT extensions.id_encode(1, 'mysalt'); -- 'Rj' (custom salt for security)

-- Decode string → integer
SELECT extensions.id_decode('jR');        -- ARRAY[1]
SELECT extensions.id_decode('Lw');        -- ARRAY[100]
```

```typescript
// In Next.js — create short order URL
// Don't actually store hashids — compute on the fly from integer ID
// Use supabase.rpc() to encode/decode via the DB function

// OR install hashids npm package for client-side (same algorithm)
import Hashids from 'hashids'
const h = new Hashids(process.env.HASHIDS_SALT, 6)
const shortId = h.encode(orderId)       // number → 'k3Lp2Q'
const original = h.decode(shortId)[0]  // 'k3Lp2Q' → number
```

