## pg_graphql — GraphQL API

**When you need it**: Rocket projects that use a GraphQL client instead of supabase-js REST.
Enabled by default. **As of 2025 security update: new projects have this disabled by default.**

```
GraphQL endpoint: https://[REF].supabase.co/graphql/v1
Authorization: Bearer [ANON_KEY]
```

```graphql
# Query (auto-generated from your schema)
query {
  ordersCollection(filter: { userId: { eq: "user-uuid" } }) {
    edges {
      node {
        id
        status
        amountCents
        profiles {
          fullName
        }
      }
    }
  }
}

# Insert
mutation {
  insertIntoOrdersCollection(objects: [{ userId: "...", amountCents: 4999 }]) {
    records { id }
  }
}
```

```typescript
// Use with any GraphQL client
import { createClient as createUrqlClient } from 'urql'
const urql = createUrqlClient({
  url: `${process.env.NEXT_PUBLIC_SUPABASE_URL}/graphql/v1`,
  fetchOptions: { headers: { apikey: process.env.NEXT_PUBLIC_SUPABASE_ANON_KEY! } }
})
```

**Security**: RLS applies to GraphQL exactly like REST. If you don't use GraphQL, disable it:
```sql
DROP EXTENSION IF EXISTS pg_graphql;
-- Or: Dashboard → Database → Extensions → pg_graphql → toggle OFF
```

