## pg_trgm — Fuzzy Text Search

**When you need it**: Search that tolerates typos. "similiar" finds "similar". Search-as-you-type autocomplete. Short strings where full-text search is too strict.

```sql
CREATE EXTENSION IF NOT EXISTS pg_trgm WITH SCHEMA extensions;

-- GIN index for fast trigram search
CREATE INDEX products_name_trgm_idx ON products USING gin(name gin_trgm_ops);
CREATE INDEX profiles_email_trgm_idx ON profiles USING gin(email gin_trgm_ops);

-- Fuzzy search (% operator = similarity threshold)
SELECT name, similarity(name, 'iphone') AS score
FROM products
WHERE name % 'iphone'   -- similarity > 0.3 (default threshold)
ORDER BY score DESC
LIMIT 10;

-- ILIKE with index support (normally ILIKE can't use B-tree indexes)
SELECT * FROM profiles WHERE email ILIKE '%john%';
-- With GIN trgm index, this ILIKE is now fast
```

```typescript
// From supabase-js — use .filter() for trigram similarity
const { data } = await supabase
  .from('products')
  .select('name')
  .filter('name', 'ilike', `%${query}%`)   // uses trgm GIN index
  .limit(10)
```

