## PGAudit — Database-Level Audit Logging

**When you need it**: Compliance (HIPAA, SOC2, GDPR), tracking who accessed what data, security audits. Different from an application-level audit_log trigger — PGAudit captures ALL database access including direct connections.

```sql
CREATE EXTENSION IF NOT EXISTS pgaudit WITH SCHEMA extensions;

-- Log all SELECT statements for the authenticated role
ALTER ROLE authenticated SET pgaudit.log = 'read';

-- Log writes for all roles
ALTER DATABASE postgres SET pgaudit.log = 'write';

-- Log everything (use sparingly — generates huge logs)
ALTER DATABASE postgres SET pgaudit.log = 'all';

-- pgaudit.log options:
-- read     = SELECT, COPY
-- write    = INSERT, UPDATE, DELETE, TRUNCATE, COPY
-- function = function calls
-- role     = GRANT, REVOKE, CREATE ROLE
-- ddl      = CREATE, ALTER, DROP
-- misc     = DISCARD, FETCH, CHECKPOINT
-- all      = everything above
```

Logs appear in: Supabase Dashboard → Logs → Postgres Logs.

