## PostGIS — Geospatial Queries

**When you need it**: "Restaurants near me", delivery radius, distance calculations, map features.

```sql
CREATE EXTENSION IF NOT EXISTS postgis WITH SCHEMA extensions;

-- Add location column to a table
ALTER TABLE restaurants ADD COLUMN location GEOGRAPHY(POINT, 4326);

-- Insert a location (longitude, latitude — note order!)
UPDATE restaurants
SET location = ST_SetSRID(ST_MakePoint(-73.9857, 40.7484), 4326)
WHERE id = 'restaurant-uuid';

-- Find restaurants within 5km of a point
SELECT name, ST_Distance(location, ST_MakePoint(-73.98, 40.75)::geography) AS distance_meters
FROM restaurants
WHERE ST_DWithin(
  location,
  ST_MakePoint(-73.98, 40.75)::geography,  -- user location (lng, lat)
  5000                                       -- 5000 meters = 5km radius
)
ORDER BY distance_meters;

-- Add spatial index for fast distance queries
CREATE INDEX restaurants_location_idx ON restaurants USING gist(location);
```

```typescript
// From supabase-js — use rpc() for spatial queries
const { data } = await supabase.rpc('nearby_restaurants', {
  lat: userLat, lng: userLng, radius_meters: 5000
})
```

